The White House has announced that the 2011 White House Easter Egg Roll will take place on April 25th, with the theme of "Get Up and Go!" The event aims to promote health and wellness, with activities such as live music, sports courts, cooking stations, storytelling, and Easter egg rolling. The event is part of the First Lady's 'Let's Move!' initiative, which aims to combat childhood obesity. Tickets will be distributed through an online lottery system, and the event is open to children aged 12 and younger and their families. More information can be found on the official White House website.